      <title>Re: Trophy Certificates giving xp to the trophy now, is this how it works?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12312#M12312</link>
      <description>Redoing the trophy isn't a big deal, if you take your time.  Every day or two, do some subcombines for the trophy and set them aside.  When you have them all done over the course of a few days and materials gathered and ready, destroy your current trophy and go and request the task again.   As long as you have some extra ingredients incase of failures, it shouldn't take you too long.  I know every tradeskill has differing levels of difficulty on the test as far as obtaining materials; however, the expert fletching trophy took me all of one hour to redo after I had saved up enough parts (that includes travelling to and from WFP and to the bazaar when I failed too many times on the GM trophy).&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
