      <description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Xianzu_Monk_Tunare wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;If you bother to equip the trophy as you do your skill ups it actually levels with you so it's pointless to waste time and money redoing the trophy test when all the combines in it will be trivial to you except for possibly 1 or 2.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;An option?  Yes.  Pointless?  No.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It depends on your skill level.  At 282 Fletching, I now have 64% on my trophy because I chose to redo it.  I am now up to 67%, and will be 70% after my next run.  I estimate that the trophy will hit Master before me, when I get to about 297 skill.  That is perfect, because if I hit master before my trophy, due to the fact that I will be doing so few 300+ fletching combines, it will be quite hard to have the fletching trophy skill-up naturally.  I would not want to waste a single fletching combine on catching-up my trophy to master level.  If I left it at 0% and had not redone the quest, I would hit master fletcher somewhere around 35% on my trophy.  That means I would have had to do a good 70 to 100 combines still after I became a master fletcher to get the trophy to master's level at the 10x's catch-up rate.  No thanks.  I'll take that xp on my master's trophy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
